From 403e5fd022e7a3b83db7b6bce7b33f952c87ec04 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 10:33:13 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Add Calendar tab, note version history, PWA
 install/offline support, and wiki-style note linking
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Calendar: new sidebar tab (own route, not merged into Tasks/Issues)
  showing a month grid aggregating Task and Issue due dates, with a
  day-detail panel and click-through to the source item.

- Notes version history: every note keeps a throttled snapshot trail
  (one per 10-minute window of edits) in a new NoteVersion table. A
  History panel on the note lists past versions with one-click restore;
  restoring itself snapshots the current state first, so it's undoable.

- PWA: installable manifest + SVG icon (works at any size, no build
  tooling needed) and a hand-written service worker that caches the
  built app shell for resilience against flaky connections. API and
  upload requests are always network-only — nothing sensitive is cached.

- Wiki-style [[links]] between notes, the highest-care item of this
  batch:
    - Typing [[ opens a live autocomplete of matching note titles, with
      a "Create note" fallback when nothing matches.
    - Each text block is click-to-edit / blur-to-view, same pattern as
      title editing elsewhere: view mode renders [[links]] as clickable
      pills (dashed/muted style for links to notes that don't exist yet
      — clicking one creates and opens that note).
    - A "Linked from" backlinks panel shows which notes reference the
      current one.
    - Renaming a note automatically rewrites [[oldTitle]] to
      [[newTitle]] in every note that links to it, so links never
      silently break.
    - Fixed a block key collision (getBlocks() was handing out the
      same literal 'legacy' id for every note's default block) that
      caused the editor to keep stale edit/view state when switching
      between notes with no custom blocks yet.

Also translated a handful of tooltips/titles missed in the previous
PT-PT/EN pass (Notes "New Note" button, Passwords reveal/copy, Issues
status color swatch, AI Agents launcher, color wheel hint).
